# Job Structure

Two patterns exist for organizing jobs:

## Leaf jobs

Simple jobs live directly in `jobs/<name>/index.ts` (e.g. `jobs/cinnamon/`).

## Provider groups

Jobs that share infrastructure (auth, API client) are grouped under a provider directory with nested subfolders per job:

```
jobs/spotify/
  auth.ts                    # shared auth logic
  api.ts                     # shared API client
  types.ts                   # shared types (e.g. SpotifyProfileResponse)
  recently-played/
    index.ts                 # entrypoint
    ingest.ts                # job logic
    types.ts                 # job-specific types and payload
  top-tracks/
    index.ts
    ingest.ts
    types.ts
```

## Conventions

- `jobs/_shared/` contains utilities shared across all jobs (e.g. `isDirectExecution`). Prefixed with `_` so the job runner skips it.
- Every job entrypoint (`index.ts`) must use `isDirectExecution(import.meta.url)` to support standalone execution via `bun run jobs/<path>/index.ts`.
- `jobs/native-handlers.ts` maps BullMQ job names to hand-coded TypeScript handler functions. Config-driven jobs are defined in `cinnamon.config.ts` and merged into the unified registry at `config/dynamic-registry.ts`.
- Job-specific types go in the job's own `types.ts`. Shared provider types stay at the provider level.
- Use `../api.ts` and `../auth.ts` for shared provider imports within nested jobs. Use `@/db/...` and `@/config/...` for cross-directory imports.
